<h2><a name="empty" id="empty">empty</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;list&gt;</span>
    bool empty<span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="kw4">const</span>;</pre>
<p>
The empty() function returns true if the list has no elements, false
otherwise.  For example, the following code uses empty() as the
stopping condition on a <a href="../../keywords/while" class="wikilink1" title="keywords:while">while</a> loop to clear a list and
display its contents in reverse order:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">   list<span class="sy0">&lt;</span>int<span class="sy0">&gt;</span> v;
   <span class="kw1">for</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">int</span> i <span class="sy0">=</span> <span class="nu19">0</span>; i <span class="sy0">&lt;</span> <span class="nu0">5</span>; i<span class="sy0">++</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="br0">&#123;</span>
     v.<span class="me1">push_back</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span>i<span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
   <span class="br0">&#125;</span>
   <span class="kw1">while</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="sy0">!</span>v.<span class="me1">empty</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="br0">&#123;</span>
     <a href="http://www.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009695399/functions/cout.html"><span class="kw3">cout</span></a> <span class="sy0">&lt;&lt;</span> v.<span class="me1">back</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="sy0">&lt;&lt;</span> endl;
     v.<span class="me1">pop_back</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
   <span class="br0">&#125;</span></pre>
<p>

Related Topics: <a href="size" class="wikilink1" title="stl:list:size">size</a>
</p>

